Imo State Governor, Senator Hope Uzodinma has approved the appointment of sixteen more Special Assistants and Senior Special Assistants into his cabinet. In a release signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Oguwuike Nwachukwu, the appointments were with immediate effect. According to the release, eight of the sixteen appointees were SAs. Similarly, the Governor will on Monday, at the government house, swear in the 22 commissioner-nominees who have been cleared by the State House of Assembly.